<ol>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Log on to the tenant agent interface&nbsp;as <b>tenant admin</b> user. The tenant agent interface URL was derived in earlier steps.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<ol start="2">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Tenant dashboard is displayed. The dashboard is the default homepage for every user, but it is configurable and can be changed.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/b/bb/CGRO-DashboardHomepage.PNG" height="427" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395a97015bd1.23330465.png" style="width: 800px; height: 427px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></p>

<ol start="3">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">From the <b>mega menu</b> (<b>Three horizontal lines</b> icon), navigate to <b>Administration</b> -&gt; <b>Configuration</b> -&gt; <b>Application Settings</b></span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/4e/CGRO-MegaAdminAppSettings.PNG" height="324" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395b3f0d17a0.34259267.png" style="width: 800px; height: 324px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></p>

<ol start="4">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the <b>APPLICATION SETTINGS</b> screen, turn on the <b>Enable Cost Governance and Resource Optimization</b> setting.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/7/71/CGRO-AppSettingsCGRO.PNG" height="764" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395c797680c1.60199996.png" style="width: 800px; height: 764px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></span></span></span></p>

<ol start="5">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Scroll to the top of the <b>APPLICATION SETTINGS</b> screen. In the <strong>Tenant key chain</strong>&nbsp;section, if <strong>Create Key Chain</strong> option is still available, click&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Create Key Chain.&nbsp;</strong>In the <strong>Create tenant key chain</strong>&nbsp;window, type in and confirm the passcode. Click <strong>OK</strong>. A tenant key chain is required to support encrypted fields in the tenant.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/a/a7/CGRO-CreateTenantKeyChain.png" height="298" hspace="0" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/a/a7/CGRO-CreateTenantKeyChain.png" style="width:624px;height:298px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="624"></span></span></span></p>

<ol start="6">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Scroll to the top of the <b>APPLICATION SETTINGS</b> screen. Click <strong>Save.</strong></span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><strong><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/4e/CGRO-AppSettingsSave.PNG" height="511" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395ea2032d32.09702179.png" style="width: 800px; height: 511px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></strong></p>

<h3>Configure authorization for CGRO</h3>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">By default, the tenant admin account has visibility and access to CGRO functionalities. To configure CGRO authorization for other users, follow the steps below:</span></span></span></p>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Create a CGRO administration user account in the suite administration portal.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Setup&nbsp;CGRO&nbsp;administration role,&nbsp;group and CGRO admin account in the IDM portal.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Create CGRO&nbsp;role&nbsp;and associate CGRO admin account in the HCMX tenant agent interface.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<h4>Create a CGRO administration user account in suite administration portal</h4>

<ol start="1">
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Log on to the suite administration portal as user <b>suite-admin</b> at the following URL: <span class="MsoHyperlink" style="color:#0563c1"><span style="text-decoration:underline">https://&lt;HCMX-Server-FQDN&gt;/bo</span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<ol start="2">
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the <b>suite administration</b> home page, navigate to <b>USERS</b>. Click <strong>New</strong>.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/8/89/CGRO-BO-UsersHome.PNG" height="155" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60398d5e9af469.05437938.png" style="width: 800px; height: 155px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></span></span></span></p>

<ol start="3">
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the&nbsp;<strong>New user</strong>&nbsp;window, select the <strong>account&nbsp;</strong>associated with the tenant in which CGRO capability was enabled in earlier steps. Fill in the remaining information as shown in the screenshot below. Note that login name does not have to be&nbsp;<strong>cgroAdmin</strong>. Click&nbsp;<strong>SAVE</strong>. This new user account will be used to administer and use CGRO functionalities.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/c/c8/CGRO-BO-cgroAdminNewUser.PNG" height="800" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60398d5ef2faa0.88839640.png" style="width: 679.157px; height: 800px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="679.1569086651054"></p>

<ol start="4">
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">A user account activation email is sent by HCMX to the email address specified in the&nbsp;<strong>cgroAdmin</strong>&nbsp;user record. Click on the user activation link in that email. User activation web page is launched in a web browser. Type in a new password and confirm the new password in the user activation web page. Note that the&nbsp;<strong>SUBMIT</strong>&nbsp;button does not show up until entered passwords match and they satisfy password complexity policy as defined in the IDM portal.&nbsp;Click&nbsp;<strong>SUBMIT</strong>.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/0/08/08-PwdReset.png" height="326" hspace="0" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/0/08/08-PwdReset.png" style="width:490px;height:326px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="490"></p>

<h4>Setup CGRO administration role, group and CGRO admin account in the IDM portal</h4>

<ol start="1">
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Log on to the IDM administration portal as user <b>suite-admin</b> at the following URL: <a href="https://%3cHCMXServerFQDN%3e/idm-admin" style="color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline">https://&lt;HCMXServerFQDN&gt;/idm-admin</a></span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<ol start="2">
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">A list of organizations is displayed. Click on the organization that corresponds to the tenant id that was noted in earlier steps. In this example, it is the organization with tenant number <b>192661264</b>.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/6/63/CGRO-IDMOrgs-1.PNG" height="351" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_603993e23154b9.03881075.png" style="width: 800px; height: 351px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></p>

<ol start="3">
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the <b>ORGANIZATION</b> menu, Click <b>Roles</b> page. A list of existing roles is displayed. Create <b>+</b> icon to create a new role for CGRO functionality.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

